Oil GLS

Friday 19 Mar 2021

The following data on oil spills in the United States from 1973-1985 were recorded, where Oil Lost is in thousands of metric tonnes.

Year Number of Spills Total Oil Lost
1973 36 84.5
1974 48 67.1
1975 45 188.0
1976 29 204.2
1977 49 213.1
1978 35 260.5
1979 65 723.5
1980 32 135.6
1981 33 45.3
1982 9 1.7
1983 17 387.8
1984 15 24.2
1985 8 15.0

Suppose the amount of oil lost in a single spill, \(S\), are independent random variables with

\[ E(S)=\mu \mbox{ and } \var(S)=\sigma^2. \]

If \(Y\) denote the total oil lost in a year in which \(k\) spills occurred, observe that

\[ E(Y)=k\mu \mbox{ and } \var(Y)=k\sigma^2. \] Consider the linear regression model

\[ Y=\beta_0+\beta_1x+{\cal E} \]

where \(Y\) is the total oil lost and \(x\) is the number of spills for each year.
